Greater Feint	TYPE:General
Prerequisites:	INT=15, Combat Expertise, Improved Feint, base attack bonus +11.
Benefit: You can make a Bluff check to feint in combat as a swift action.
Special: A fighter may select Greater Feint as one of his fighter bonus feats.

Greater Trip	TYPE:General
Prerequisites:	INT=15, Combat Expertise, Improved Trip, base attack bonus +11.
Benefit: You gain an additional +4 bonus on your Strength check to trip your opponent (which stacks with the bonus provided by Improved Trip.
Special: A fighter may select Greater Trip as one of his fighter bonus feats.

###DAMAGE PENETRATION FAMILY

Damage Penetration (Physical)	TYPE:General
You possess a clear understanding of the defenses of monsters, and know how to overcome some of them.
Prerequisites: Fighter level 3rd.
Benefit: Whenever you deal weapon damage, you may ignore DR/bludgeoning, DR/piercing and DR/slashing, regardless of the actual type of weapon you are using.  However, Damage Penetration (Physical) alone will not overcome combined damage reduction types such as DR/bludgeoning and magic; you need to have all of the relevant Damage Penetration feats to overcome such combined types.

Damage Penetration (Alignment)	TYPE:General
You possess a clear understanding of the defenses of monsters, and know how to overcome some of them.
Prerequisites: Fighter level 6th.
Benefit: Choose a single alignment component (chaos, evil, good or law).  Whenever you deal weapon damage, you may ignore damage reduction of that alignment type.  However, Damage Penetration (Alignment) alone will not overcome combined damage reduction types such as DR/chaos and silver; you need to have all of the relevant Damage Penetration feats to overcome such combined types.

Damage Penetration (Material)	TYPE:General
You possess a clear understanding of the defenses of monsters, and know how to overcome some of them.
Prerequisites: Fighter level 9th.
Benefit: Choose a single weapon material (adamantine, cold iron, silver or wood).  Whenever you deal weapon damage, you may ignore damage reduction of that material type.  However, Damage Penetration (Material) alone will not overcome combined damage reduction types such as DR/adamantine and magic; you need to have all of the relevant Damage Penetration feats to overcome such combined types.

Damage Penetration (Magic)	TYPE:General
You possess a clear understanding of the defenses of monsters, and know how to overcome some of them.
Prerequisites: Fighter level 12th.
Benefit: Whenever you deal weapon damage, you may ignore DR/magic, regardless of whether or not you are using an actual magic weapon.  However, Damage Penetration (Magic) alone will not overcome combined damage reduction types such as DR/magic and piercing; you need to have all of the relevant Damage Penetration feats to overcome such combined types.

Damage Penetration (Alignment, All)	TYPE:General
You possess a clear understanding of the defenses of monsters, and know how to overcome some of them.
Prerequisites: Damage Penetration (Alignment), fighter level 15th.
Benefit: Whenever you deal weapon damage, you may ignore all alignment-based damage reduction.  However, Damage Penetration (Alignment, All) alone will not overcome combined damage reduction types such as DR/good and slashing; you need to have all of the relevant Damage Penetration feats to overcome such combined types.

Damage Penetration (Material, All)	TYPE:General
You possess a clear understanding of the defenses of monsters, and know how to overcome some of them.
Prerequisites: Damage Penetration (Material), fighter level 18th.
Benefit: Whenever you deal weapon damage, you may ignore all material-based damage reduction.  However, Damage Penetration (Material, All) alone will not overcome combined damage reduction types such as DR/cold iron and lawful; you need to have all of the relevant Damage Penetration feats to overcome such combined types.

Damage Penetration (Epic) [EPIC]
You possess a clear understanding of the defenses of monsters, and know how to overcome some of them.
Prerequisites: Damage Penetration (Magic), fighter level 21st.
Benefit: Whenever you deal weapon damage, you may ignore DR/epic, regardless of whether or not you are using an actual epic weapon.

Damage Penetration (All) [EPIC]
You possess a clear understanding of the defenses of monsters, and know how to overcome some of them.
Prerequisites: Damage Penetration (Physical), Damage Penetration (Alignment, All), Damage Penetration (Material, All), Damage Penetration (Epic), fighter level 24th.
Benefit: Whenever you deal weapon damage, you may ignore any and all damage reduction, including DR/-.

