###MISCELLANEOUS FAMILY

Effortless Music [SPECIAL]
Prerequisite:	WIS=13, bardic music.
Benefit: When using a bardic music effect that normally requires a standard action to maintain concentration, you may instead use a swift action.

Size Doesn'T Matter	TYPE:General
Prerequisite: Combat Expertise, Power Attack, character level 10th.
Benefit: When making opposed attack rolls or opposed Strength checks for a special attack against an opponent (such as disarm, grapple, sunder or trip), if the opponent is a larger size category than you, treat him as if he were one size category smaller than he is.
Special: You can gain this feat multiple times. Its effects stack, as long as it does not cause a larger opponent to actually be treated as a size category smaller than yours.
Designer's Notes: This feat effectively grants a +4 circumstantial bonus to opposed special attacks, but usually only against some of the more powerful monsters out there.  The reason why this feat does not merely grant an additional +4 bonus (unnamed and therefore universal) to such special attacks, is because the designer's intention was to help PCs actually have a fighting chance to grapple or trip monsters, without making them ridiculously lethal against humanoid NPCs or in PvP play.  By instead eliminating the circumstantial +4 size bonuses of larger opponents, this prevents PCs from feeling helpless in some situations (fighting a dragon), without accidentally making them over-powered in other situations (fighting a blackguard).

Trap Finder [SPECIAL]
Prerequisites:	INT=13.
Benefit: You gain the trapfinding ability of a rogue, and may add Disable Device, Open Lock and Search to all of your classes' skills list.

Wild Empath [SPECIAL]
Prerequisites:	WIS=13
Benefit: You gain the wild empathy ability as a druid of half your character level (which stacks with levels of classes that grant wild empathy), and may add Handle Animal, Ride and Survival to all of your classes' skills list.

