###WHIP USE FAMILY

Improved Whip Use	TYPE:General
Prerequisites: Proficiency with the whip, base attack bonus +3.
Benefit: You no longer provoke attacks of opportunity for using a whip.  In addition, you are able to use a whip to make attacks of opportunity within 5 feet of yourself.
Normal: Using a whip provokes an attack of opportunity, and a whip cannot be used to make an attack of opportunity.

Greater Whip Use	TYPE:General
Prerequisites: Proficiency with the whip, Improved Whip Use, base attack bonus +6.
Benefit: You are able to deal damage normally, even to creatures with an armor bonus of +1 or higher or creatures with a natural armor bonus of +3 or higher, and may choose to deal lethal damage instead of nonlethal damage.  In addition, you are able to use a whip to make attacks of opportunity within 10 feet of yourself.
Normal: A whip is unable to deal damage to creatures with an armor bonus of +1 or higher or creatures with a natural armor bonus of +3 or higher, and is only able to deal nonlethal damage.

Supreme Whip Use	TYPE:General
Prerequisites: Proficiency with the whip, Improved Whip Use, Greater Whip Use, base attack bonus +9.
Benefit: You are able to use a whip almost like a third hand – in general, you use move-equivalent actions to make an attack roll against a DC of 15-20 (or higher if your DM deems a task sufficiently difficult) to accomplish such things as pushing a button, snuffing a candle, retrieving an unattended object, attaching onto fixtures to jump and swing across a room, or grabbing a projection to catch yourself from a fall.  In addition, you are able to use a whip to make attacks of opportunity within 15 feet of yourself.
Normal: A whip is can be used to disarm or trip an opponent, but generally can not be used to perform fine or complex tasks.
